# Git workflow

Every change must be tied to a GitHub issue.

## Branch naming

Use:

`<type>/<issue-number>-<short-kebab-description>`

Allowed types:

- `feature`
- `bugfix`
- `fix`
- `refactor`
- `test`
- `docs`
- `chore`

Examples:

- `feature/42-add-user-auth`
- `bugfix/87-fix-null-track-state`
- `refactor/103-split-fusion-service`
- `test/118-add-parser-regression-tests`

## Commit messages

Use Conventional Commit style and include the issue number.

Format:

`<type>(#<issue-number>): <imperative summary>`

Examples:

- `fix(#87): handle missing sensor timestamp`
- `feature(#42): add user auth endpoint`
- `test(#118): add parser regression coverage`
- `refactor(#103): split fusion service initialization`

## Pull requests

PR title format:

`<type>(#<issue-number>): <summary>`

PR body must include:

`Closes #<issue-number>`

Example:

`Closes #87`

Use one issue per PR unless the issues are tightly coupled.
